                <h1>Activist CeCe McDonald takes allies to task in public talk</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/3d6cf5ed-160f-4ada-974b-a1fcfa6dabff.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="CeCe&#x20;McDonald,&#x20;pictured&#x20;in&#x20;San&#x20;Francisco&#x20;in&#x20;2015,&#x20;visited&#x20;Durham&#x20;last&#x20;Sunday&#x20;for&#x20;&quot;Evening&#x20;Tea&#x20;with&#x20;CeCe&#x20;McDonald,&quot;&#x20;which&#x20;was&#x20;sponsored&#x20;by&#x20;the&#x20;LGBTQ&#x20;Center&#x20;of&#x20;Durham&#x20;and&#x20;the&#x20;Center&#x20;for&#x20;Sexual&#x20;and&#x20;Gender&#x20;Diversity&#x20;at&#x20;Duke." class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            CeCe McDonald, pictured in San Francisco in 2015, visited Durham last Sunday for "Evening Tea with CeCe McDonald," which was sponsored by the LGBTQ Center of Durham and the Center for Sexual and Gender Diversity at Duke.

                                                             <aside class="photo-caption photo-credit d-block pl-1">
                                    <figcaption class="d-block">
